The 785 new infections recorded in the last 24 to 48 hours have also come with zero fatalities, as announced by the National Institute for Communicable Diseases on Monday evening. The cumulative number of infections in the currently stands at 3 974 042 and fatalities at 99 412 as the country is on the countdown to the expiry of the National State of Disaster on March 15. A total of 13 669 tests have been conducted in the last 24 hours with a positivity rate of 5.7%. The country currently only has just more than 31 000 active cases. --SABC--